{"type":"user","uuid":"2641733f-7f96-4266-b53f-3106ce3b559c","session_id":"6fb936db-bc01-420e-86f4-854e69bc802e","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde4cc82da792f3c08ce5cc299341","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 36 integration tests pass. Now let me compile the final code review report.\n\n---\n\n# F-002 Code Review Report\n\n## Verdict: **PASS_WITH_WARNINGS**\n\n---\n\n## Spec Compliance Summary\n\n| User Story | Status | Acceptance Criteria |\n|------------|--------|---------------------|\n| **US-1: Pipeline Command** | ✅ PASS | Supports run/status/logs/stop subcommands, target param optional, --type option, invalid subcommand returns help |\n| **US-2: Bugfix Command** | ✅ PASS | Equivalent to `/pipeline run --type=bugfix`, missing param returns usage |\n| **US-3: Status Query** | ✅ PASS | Returns pipeline list + status summary, no pipelines returns helpful message |\n| **US-4: Logs Query** | ✅ PASS | Implements 4000 char threshold for file sending (per D3) |\n| **US-5: Stop Pipeline** | ✅ PASS | Returns stop confirmation |\n| **US-6: Error Guidance** | ✅ PASS | Clear error messages with suggestions and correct command examples |\n| **US-7: Authorization Guard** | ✅ PASS | All commands have `requiresAuth: true`, uses `isAllowedUser()`, unified rejection message |\n\n---\n\n## Plan Compliance Summary\n\n| Component | Status | Notes |\n|-----------|--------|-------|\n| Parser (`parser.js`) | ✅ | Parses command, subcommand, args, options, aliases |\n| Registry (`registry.js`) | ✅ | Dynamic registration, alias mapping, help text generation |\n| Validator (`validator.js`) | ✅ | Required params, type checking, enum validation |\n| Formatter (`formatter.js`) | ✅ | Error codes defined, user-friendly messages |\n| Handlers | ✅ | All 6 handlers implemented (pipeline, bugfix, planner, status, logs, stop) |\n| Integration (`telegram.js`) | ✅ | Commands registered, routeCommand middleware integrated |\n\n---\n\n## Test Coverage Summary\n\n| Test File | Tests | Status |\n|-----------|-------|--------|\n| `parser.test.js` | 18 | ✅ PASS |\n| `registry.test.js` | 14 | ✅ PASS |\n| `validator.test.js` | 14 | ✅ PASS |\n| `formatter.test.js` | 10 | ✅ PASS |\n| `handlers/handlers.test.js` | 14 | ✅ PASS |\n| `f002-command-router.integration.test.js` | 6 | ✅ PASS |\n| `f002-user-stories.integration.test.js` | 36 | ✅ PASS |\n| **Total** | **112** | **✅ ALL PASS** |\n\n---\n\n## Findings\n\n### HIGH Severity (2)\n\n#### F-001: Parser treats first positional arg as subcommand for non-subcommand commands\n- **File**: `src/bot/commands/parser.js:76-83`\n- **Issue**: Commands like `/bugfix session-123` are parsed with `subcommand='session-123'` instead of `args=['session-123']`\n- **Mitigation**: Handlers use `params._args?.[0]` fallback, so functionality works correctly\n- **Recommendation**: Consider improving parser to distinguish between subcommands and positional args based on command metadata\n\n#### F-002: Validator's getParamValue incomplete for positional args\n- **File**: `src/bot/commands/validator.js:102-115`\n- **Issue**: Function has TODO comment and doesn't properly map positional args to named params\n- **Mitigation**: Handlers work around this by using `params._args` fallback\n- **Recommendation**: Complete the positional arg mapping logic\n\n### MEDIUM Severity (3)\n\n#### F-003: Registry doesn't detect command name conflicting with existing alias\n- **File**: `src/bot/commands/registry.js:68-69`\n- **Issue**: Registering a command named `p` when `p` is already an alias for `pipeline` would be allowed\n- **Recommendation**: Add check `if (aliasToCommand.has(nameLower)) throw Error(...)`\n\n#### F-004: Missing authorization test coverage\n- **Issue**: Integration tests don't verify the authorization guard with unauthorized users\n- **Note**: `isAllowedUser()` is called correctly in `routeCommand()` and US-7.1 test verifies `requiresAuth` flag\n\n#### F-005: Duplicate formatErrorResponse function\n- **Files**: `src/bot/commands/formatter.js:127-139`, `src/bot/commands/index.js:103-115`\n- **Issue**: Same function defined in two files\n- **Recommendation**: Consolidate to formatter.js only\n\n### LOW Severity (2)\n\n#### F-006: Planner missing stop subcommand (intentional)\n- **File**: `src/bot/commands/handlers/planner.js:17-21`\n- **Issue**: Per spec, planner only has run/status/logs subcommands (stop is via `/pipeline stop --type=planner`)\n- **Status**: Working as designed per spec.md\n\n#### F-007: Markdown code blocks in log output\n- **File**: `src/bot/commands/handlers/logs.js:79`\n- **Issue**: Uses markdown code blocks which may not render correctly in all Telegram clients\n- **Recommendation**: Consider plain text format for broader compatibility\n\n---\n\n## Security Review\n\n| Check | Status |\n|-------|--------|\n| Authorization guard present | ✅ All commands check `isAllowedUser()` |\n| Sensitive info not exposed in errors | ✅ UNAUTHORIZED message doesn't reveal IDs |\n| Command injection risk | ✅ Commands use typed params, not shell |\n| Input validation | ✅ Type checking, enum validation |\n\n---\n\n## Non-Functional Requirements\n\n| NFR | Status | Evidence |\n|-----|--------|----------|\n| NFR-1: Extensibility | ✅ PASS | Registry supports dynamic command registration, aliases |\n| NFR-2: Testability | ✅ PASS | Handler interfaces mockable, 112 tests |\n| NFR-3: Performance | ✅ PASS | 1000 command parses in <100ms |\n\n---\n\n## Decisions Verification\n\n| Decision | Status |\n|----------|--------|\n| D1: `/planner` as independent type | ✅ Verified in plannerMeta and tests |\n| D2: Uses `isAllowedUser()` | ✅ Verified in routeCommand() |\n| D3: Logs >= 4000 chars as file | ✅ Verified in logs.js FILE_THRESHOLD |\n\n---\n\n## COMPLETION_SIGNAL\n\n**Feature**: F-002 Telegram Pipeline Command Router  \n**Verdict**: PASS_WITH_WARNINGS  \n**Findings**: 2 HIGH, 3 MEDIUM, 2 LOW  \n**Test Results**: 112/112 tests passing  \n**Recommendation**: Can proceed to next phase. HIGH findings have mitigations in place and don't affect functionality. Consider addressing in future iteration.\n\n[Agent ID: agent-baba934c]"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde4cc82da792f3c08ce5cc299341","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T19:11:20.010Z","_requestId":"bda469657e06472692956116ae268e6f"}
